    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-08-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-08-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="757"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d757">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 815.51/301.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Chargé d’Affaires</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 232.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Tegucigalpa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-08-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 30, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to report that, by an executive
                    order dated August 29, 1911, Mr. Zemurray is empowered to negotiate in the
                    United States, for the Government of Honduras, a loan of $500,000 in gold, the
                    proceeds thereof to be used to defray the expenses of the recent war, which the
                    Provisional Government considers itself bound to liquidate in accordance with
                    the bases of peace signed at the Conference in Puerto Cortes in May last.</p>
                <p>Mr. Zemurray left Tegucigalpa immediately thereafter, for Puerto Cortes and
                    Ceiba. Thence he intends to go direct to Washington to acquaint the Department
                    with the terms of the matter.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">J. Butler Wright</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
